genresAdvancedInfo.name: italian contemporary jazz
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Italian contemporary jazz is a genre of music that combines the improvisational nature of jazz with modern Italian influences. It features the works of contemporary Italian jazz musicians such as Enrico Rava and Stefano Bollani, and is characterized by its fusion of traditional jazz elements with Italian folk music, pop, and rock. The result is a unique and vibrant sound that reflects the rich cultural heritage of Italy.
